            <h1>How I Found My First Subject Matter Expert (SME)</h1>
            <br>
            Owning a small business requires you to multitask unlike any other position I know. You do it all: Finance, Marketing, Business Development,               Operations, Human Resources, and more. It is exhilarating but exhausting. Even if you have a core team or board of advisors, you occasionally need to venture outside your company for guidance on how to improve your business.<br>
            <br>
            At each stage of business, you need different types of expert advice. For example, in the Infancy stage, you may need help with the basics of How to Begin, and in the Quick Growth stage you may need help with the nuances of How to Scale. At every stage, you need to evaluate where you are and how you can get to the Next Level. Staying motionless isn’t an option because this means you are losing momentum. You probably already have an accountant and attorney, but who can you think through the pros and cons of expanding your business to a new location or into a new adjacent market? Who can you talk to without worrying your loved ones at night with office talk? Who can you communicate with about your doubts and concerns?<br>
